<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Second session 
Agenda item 2 
</p>
<p><b>IMPLEMENTATION OF GENERAL ASSEMBLY RESOLUTION 60/251 
OF 15 MARCH 2006 ENTITLED &#8220;HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL&#8221; 
</b></p>
<p><b> Algeria, Azerbaijan, Bahrain, Egypt</b>&#8727;<b>, Indonesia, Iran (Islamic Republic of)</b>*<b>,  
 Jordan, Kuwait</b>*<b>, Libyan Arab Jamahiriya</b>*<b>, Malaysia, Mali, Morocco,  
 Pakistan (on behalf of the Organization of the Islamic Conference),  
 Palestine</b>*<b>, Qatar</b>*<b>, Saudi Arabia, Senegal, Syrian Arab Republic</b>*<b>  
  and Tunisia:  draft decision 
</b></p>
<p><b> 2006/&#8230; Incitement to racial and religious hatred and  
  the promotion of tolerance </b></p>
<p><i> The Human Rights Council</i>, 
</p>
<p><i> Recalling</i> its decision 1/107 of 30 June 2006, 
</p>
<p><i> Taking</i> <i>into account</i> the statements made during its second session expressing deep 
concern over the increasing trend of defamation of religions, incitement to racial and religious 
hatred and its recent manifestations, 
</p>
<p>                                                 
</p>
<p>&#8727;  Non-member States of the Human Rights Council. 
</p>
<p>GE.06-14378  (E)    031006 </p>

 <p></p>
<p> <i>Taking note with appreciation </i>of the report by the Special Rapporteur on contemporary 
forms of racism, racial discrimination, xenophobia and related intolerance on the situation of 
Muslim and Arab peoples in various parts of the world (E/CN.4/2006/17), 
</p>
<p><i> Taking note</i> of the report of the Special Rapporteur on freedom of religion and belief and 
the Special Rapporteur on contemporary forms of racism, racial discrimination, xenophobia and 
related intolerance (A/HRC/2/3) as well as the report of the United Nations High Commissioner 
for Human Rights regarding this phenomenon (A/HRC/2/6), inter alia its implications for 
article 20, paragraph 2, of the International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights, 
</p>
<p><i> Decides</i> to continue substantive consideration of this matter at its third and subsequent 
sessions. 
</p>
<p>----- </p>

